Title: Pain and Gain Official Trailer #1 (2013) - Michael Bay Movie HD
Comment:
This is the first time where i do not understand why so many people hate this movie. Perhaps its the black humor and false expectations. I came in not knowing anything about the movie except that it was based around some bodybuilder.

¬†I don't feel like the depiction of the characters such as the victim demonstrate that he deserved what was coming for him, or that the the gang were good guys. You see how the supposed protagonists such as the cops treat the victim awfully -- his overall abuse and sustained injuries made me feel sad for him. And you eventually see the vices of each gang member, especially that of Wahlberg's.¬†

This movie has clearly stated that it has been exaggerated and loosely inspired by real-life events. It is by no means a documentary. If you want to complain about it's accuracy, then you should complain about other films such as The Departed, 300 etc. Most movies based on ancient history are much more historically incorrect than what i've read about the Sun Gym Gang.

Also the real life victim worked as the accountant for the production of this film and wanted to sue Mark Wahlberg (why him and not the director?) for his portrayal of himself. It sounds like he wants to cash in on the movie profits to me.

Overall this film slightly deviates away from the cliche slapstick comedy that we see so often today by injecting black humour into it. It is a refreshing change.
